.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-api_tester \- A lightweight CLI HTTP client for running one-off requests or saving and replaying reusable request profiles, with timing breakdowns and formatted response output.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility api_tester
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A lightweight CLI HTTP client for running one-off requests or saving and replaying reusable request profiles, with timing breakdowns and formatted response output.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBOne-off requests\fP — fire a quick HTTP request without saving anything
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSaved profiles\fP — store named request configurations and replay them later
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTiming breakdown\fP — shows DNS, TCP, TTFB, and total time for every request
.IP \(bu 4
\fBJSON formatting\fP — pretty-prints JSON responses automatically using \fCjq\fP if available
.IP \(bu 4
\fBStatus code coloring\fP — green for 2xx, yellow for 3xx, red for 4xx/5xx
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --method GET --url https://api.example.com/items

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --method POST --url https://api.example.com/items \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --body '{"name":"demo"}'

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --method POST --url https://api.example.com/items \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --body-file ./payload.json

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --save staging-users \
  --method GET --url https://staging.example.com/users \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer TOKEN'

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --run staging-users

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --show staging-users

bash _api_tester/_api_tester.sh --list
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--method METHOD\fP   |   HTTP method (default: \fCGET\fP)
\fC--url URL\fP   |   Request URL including protocol
\fC--header 'K: V'\fP   |   Request header (can be repeated for multiple headers)
\fC--body TEXT\fP   |   Request body as inline text
\fC--body-file FILE\fP   |   Request body read from a file
\fC--save NAME\fP   |   Save the request as a named profile
\fC--run NAME\fP   |   Execute a previously saved profile
\fC--show NAME\fP   |   Print the contents of a saved profile
\fC--list\fP   |   List all saved profile names
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH REQUEST OUTPUT
.PP
.EX
  Request
  ------------------------------------------------
  Method:  GET
  URL:     https://api.example.com/items
  Header:  Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

  Timing
  ------------------------------------------------
  Status:  200
  DNS:     0.012s
  TCP:     0.034s
  TTFB:    0.187s
  Total:   0.201s

  Response body
  ------------------------------------------------
  {
    "items": [
      { "id": 1, "name": "demo" }
    ]
  }
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH SAVED PROFILES
.PP
Profiles are stored as plain bash variable files under:
.PP
.EX
~/.local/share/utilitykit/api_profiles/
.EE
.PP
Each profile captures the method, URL, headers, and body so it can be replayed exactly with \fC--run\fP.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCcurl\fP — required for all requests
.IP \(bu 4
\fCjq\fP — optional, used for JSON pretty-printing
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Missing URL, profile not found, or \fCcurl\fP not installed
